main event: A bright white round object was observed rising on the horizon in Superior, Wisconsin on August 9, 1963.
interesting points: The object exhibited erratic motion, moving both up and down as well as side to side,The observation lasted for 20 minutes before the object cleared out of sight,The sighting occurred at night,The report indicated that the observation might be a balloon due to the described motion,The object seemed to have edges and depth.
